Module kivakit.component
Package com.telenav.kivakit.component

Interface Component

All Superinterfaces:
Broadcaster, LanguageTrait, Listener, NamedObject, PackagePathTrait, Receiver, RegistryTrait, Repeater, ResourceTrait, SettingsTrait, Transceiver, Transmitter, TryTrait
All Known Subinterfaces:
ComponentFunction<From,​To>, ComponentMixin, ComponentSupplier<Value>
All Known Implementing Classes:
Application, BaseComponent, Server
public interface Component extends Repeater, NamedObject, SettingsTrait, RegistryTrait, PackagePathTrait, TryTrait, LanguageTrait, ResourceTrait
Interface to KivaKit component functionality, including easy access to settings (see Settings) and object registries (see Registry).

Packaging Methods

Classes implementing this interface are provided with easy access to packages and package resources relative to the class' package:

  • ResourceTrait.packageResource(String) - Returns a Resource for the given path relative to the class implementing this interface
  • ResourceTrait.relativePackage(String) - Returns a KivaKit Package for the given path relative to the class implementing this interface

Settings Registry Methods

Settings for a component can be retrieved with SettingsTrait.settingsRegistry(). This provides a simplified interface to load settings objects specified by the user while also allowing for default settings when they are not specified. See Settings for details.

  • SettingsTrait.settingsRegistry() - Retrieves the Settings registry for this component
  • SettingsTrait.lookupSettings(Class) - A settings object of the specified class or null if none exists
  • SettingsTrait.lookupSettings(Class, Enum) - Get any given instance of the given settings object type
  • SettingsTrait.lookupSettings(Class, String) - Get any given instance of the given settings object type
  • SettingsTrait.requireSettings(Class) - Gets the given settings object or fails
  • SettingsTrait.requireSettings(Class, Enum) - Gets the settings object of the given instance or fails
  • SettingsTrait.requireSettings(Class, String) - Gets the settings object of the given instance or fails
  • #registerDeployment(Deployment) - Adds the settings objects for the given deployment
  • SettingsTrait.registerSettingsObject(Object) - Adds the given settings object
  • #registerAllSettingsIn(Settings) - Adds the settings objects in the given settings registry
  • #registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Folder) - Adds settings objects from the given folder
  • #registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Package) - Adds settings objects from the given package
  • #registerAllSettingsIn(Listener, Class, String) - Adds settings object from the package relative to the given class

Object Lookup Registry

Access to this component's lookup Registry is provided and fulfills basic needs for object wiring:

  • RegistryTrait.lookup(Class) - Lookup the registered object of the given type, if any
  • RegistryTrait.lookup(Class, String) - Find the given instance of the given class, if any
  • RegistryTrait.lookup(Class, Enum) - Find the given instance of the given class, if any
  • RegistryTrait.register(Object) - Register the given singleton object for lookup
  • RegistryTrait.register(Object, String) - Register the given instance of the given object for lookup
  • RegistryTrait.register(Object, Enum) - Register the given instance of the given object for lookup
  • RegistryTrait.registry() - Retrieves the lookup Registry for this component
